document_data.History:
Going by her age, the Lady was born around [[1289 DR]]. Both her real name and her history were unknown to others, and she was known only as the Lady or the Green Lady for many years.{{Cite dungeon/75/Into the Nest of Vipers|73}}

It was known, however, that she settled in the [[Misty Vale]] in Brynwood in the Vast around [[1349 DR]], where she went into semi-retirement and lived in seclusion.

On 28th [[Eleasias]] of [[1369 DR|the Year of the Gauntlet, 1369 DR]], [[Dura Gerathu]], a [[ranger]] friend of the Lady, visited her to tell how he'd discovered the [[Vipers' Nest]]. She advised him to watch the place longer and learn all he could, but this led to Dura being murdered by the [[Vipers]] bandits. The bandits followed Dura's writings and came after the Lady next. Forewarned by the [[Sprite (creature)|sprites]] she lived with, she conjured obscuring mists and illusory forests to drive the terrified bandits off. [[Calispar Delgorth]], the leader of the assault, vowed to return and finish her later.{{Cite dungeon/75/Into the Nest of Vipers|72}}

Afterwards, the Lady sent two sprites to check on Dura, who reported his death. At the sad news, she fell into deep mourning, not eating, sleeping, nor speaking. She waited for the Vipers to return and kill her too.As [[Dungeon magazine 75|"Into the Nest of Vipers"]] is an adventure module, these events are officially unresolved. Successful progress would see the PCs rouse the Lady and defeat the Vipers.
